From cou.: 8 In line with the same procedure successfully applied to study the succ–[C12 alkyl spacer]–ni thread in solution17,18 we modelled the rotaxane using the standard Gromos96 force field22 in conjunction with atomic point charges refined by means of Density Functional Theory (DFT) calculations23 with the popular Becke's three-parameter Lee–Yang–Parr exchange functional (B3LYP).24 Obviously, at variance with our previous investigations,17 the charge distribution of the macrocycle was to be defined. Therefore, we introduced in the force field parameters for the bamgroup the point charges as obtained by applying the RESP fitting procedure25 in conjunction with the optimized geometry at B3LYP/6-31G*/CPCM level of theory and related converged electronic wavefunction. In this respect, before doing any classical/statistical sampling in dilute solution, CPCM19 represents a reasonable and well-known computational tool for evaluating the polarization of the surrounding environment on a solute molecule in its own electronic ground state.26 DFT(B3LYP)-CPCM computations were performed using the Gaussian03 package.27
From Soup: 8 In line with the same procedure successfully applied to study the succ –[C 12 alkyl spacer]– ni thread in solution 17,18 we modelled the rotaxane using the standard Gromos96 force field 22 in conjunction with atomic point charges refined by means of Density Functional Theory (DFT) calculations 23 with the popular Becke's three-parameter Lee–Yang–Parr exchange functional (B3LYP). 24 Obviously, at variance with our previous investigations, 17 the charge distribution of the macrocycle was to be defined. Therefore, we introduced in the force field parameters for the bam group the point charges as obtained by applying the RESP fitting procedure 25 in conjunction with the optimized geometry at B3LYP/6-31G*/CPCM level of theory and related converged electronic wavefunction. In this respect, before doing any classical/statistical sampling in dilute solution, CPCM 19 represents a reasonable and well-known computational tool for evaluating the polarization of the surrounding environment on a solute molecule in its own electronic ground state. 26 DFT(B3LYP)-CPCM computations were performed using the Gaussian03 package. 27
