From cou.: 9 The investigated system was then gradually heated from 50 K to 298 K using short (100 ps) MD simulations upon solvent relaxation via the steepest descent algorithm. After equilibration, a fully-classical MD trajectory was then propagated up to 100 ns using an integration step of 2.0 fs. The temperature was kept constant applying the Berendsen thermostat28 (with a time constant of 0.2 ps). Long range electrostatic interactions were computed by the Particle Mesh Ewald (PME) method,29 with 34 wave vectors in each dimension and a 4th order cubic interpolation. A cut-off of 1.1 nm was used for nonbonded interactions and the pair list was updated every 5 integration steps. All the MD simulations were carried out using the Gromacs software.30
From Soup: 9 The investigated system was then gradually heated from 50 K to 298 K using short (100 ps) MD simulations upon solvent relaxation via the steepest descent algorithm. After equilibration, a fully-classical MD trajectory was then propagated up to 100 ns using an integration step of 2.0 fs. The temperature was kept constant applying the Berendsen thermostat 28 (with a time constant of 0.2 ps). Long range electrostatic interactions were computed by the Particle Mesh Ewald ( PME ) method, 29 with 34 wave vectors in each dimension and a 4th order cubic interpolation. A cut-off of 1.1 nm was used for nonbonded interactions and the pair list was updated every 5 integration steps. All the MD simulations were carried out using the Gromacs software. 30
